<?xml version="1.0"?>

<document>
	<title>Intrapancreatic compression of the common bile duct in cystic
   fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Vitullo-B-B.</author>
	<author>Rochon-L.</author>
	<author>Seemayer-T-A.</author>
	<author>Beardmore-H.</author>
	<author>de-Belle-R-C.</author>

	<source>J-Pediatr. 1978 Dec. 93(6). P 1060-1.</source>

	<abstract>We report an infant with cystic fibrosis presenting at birth with
   meconium ileus who developed prolonged cholestatic jaundice from
   compression of the common bile duct and the pancreatic duct by
   advanced pancreatic fibrosis.  Extrahepatic biliary obstruction of
   this nature has not been previously described in cystic fibrosis.</abstract>

